column8: Najib: Rising commodity prices sign of better times in 2017PUTRAJAYA, Jan 9 — Recovering commodity prices indicate that Malaysia’s economy may improve this year, Prime Minister Datuk Seri Najib Razak said today.Speaking to civil servants at the monthly Prime Minister's Department assembly, Najib pointed that prices of crude oil, palm oil and rubber had all increased compared to 2016 prices."Looking at the global scenario and the big picture, 2016 was a very challenging year," he said."But there is hope now the situation will improve in 2017," he added.sos
